who are extremely defensive

00:36:26.530 --> 00:36:29.340
and you can see that it's
coming from a place of anxiety

00:36:29.340 --> 00:36:33.290
or fear, what would you advise?

00:36:33.290 --> 00:36:35.194
What is the best
approach in your opinion?

00:36:35.194 --> 00:36:36.860
SARAH STEIN LUBRANO:
Oh, I mean, there's

00:36:36.860 --> 00:36:39.590
lots of different techniques
for dealing with defensiveness.

00:36:39.590 --> 00:36:41.256
The main thing, first
of all, is to deal

00:36:41.256 --> 00:36:42.710
with our own defensiveness.

00:36:42.710 --> 00:36:44.960
You know, our school is
about changing ourselves more

00:36:44.960 --> 00:36:47.081
than other people.

00:36:47.081 --> 00:36:49.580
I think the other thing is to
remember that we're defensive,

00:36:49.580 --> 00:36:51.770
because we often think
that our value is attached

00:36:51.770 --> 00:36:53.960
to the criticism the
person is making.

00:36:53.960 --> 00:36:56.792
So we talk a lot in
our classes, especially

00:36:56.792 --> 00:36:58.250
in our classes
around work, that we

00:36:58.250 --> 00:37:00.590
want to make the
criticisms as we have

00:37:00.590 --> 00:37:02.875
them enormously local, right?

00:37:02.875 --> 00:37:05.250
So that it's very clear to
the person as much as possible

00:37:05.250 --> 00:37:06.920
that this isn't about their
value as a human being

00:37:06.920 --> 00:37:09.170
or even necessarily whether
they're good at their job.

00:37:09.170 --> 00:37:11.270
It's just this particular
paper on line three,

00:37:11.270 --> 00:37:13.430
I wonder if we could make
it a little bit more x.

00:37:13.430 --> 00:37:14.971
So one of the things
we work on doing

00:37:14.971 --> 00:37:17.477
is making criticism
very, very local.

00:37:17.477 --> 00:37:19.310
Because the fear of a
person who's defensive

00:37:19.310 --> 00:37:22.110
is that their whole
being is being judged.

00:37:22.110 --> 00:37:24.689
It's also very good to choose
the time and place and manner

00:37:24.689 --> 00:37:25.730
where you give criticism.

00:37:25.730 --> 00:37:26.810
And sometimes it's
easier to give it,

00:37:26.810 --> 00:37:28.940
you know, out for coffee after
you've already had a nice chat.

00:37:28.940 --> 00:37:30.270
And there's lots of other ways.

00:37:30.270 --> 00:37:32.936
But that's a good starting point
sometimes to make it very local

00:37:32.936 --> 00:37:36.104
and to watch it
in ourselves, too.

